'''''Day of the Viper''''' is a [[first-person shooter]] [[video game]] published by [[Accolade (company)|Accolade]] in [[1989 in video gaming|1989]].  As the Viper robot, the player must explore five abandoned hi-tech and heavily guarded buildings in order to find and install [[floppy disk]]s. The game was compared to ''[[3D Monster Maze]]''.<ref name="STU"/><ref name="ACE2"/>

==Reception==
The game was reviewed in 1990 in ''[[Dragon (magazine)|Dragon]]'' #157 by Hartley, Patricia, and Kirk Lesser in "The Role of Computers" column. The reviewers gave the game 5 out of 5 stars.<ref name="Dragon157">{{cite journal
|title=The Role of Computers
